- Concurrency limits, quota/billing behavior, and timeout semantics of E2B (or Smithers) are real operational seams you'll only see under load — this single-command harness proves the seam exists, it doesn't stress it.

# L2 — Provider Routing and Cancellation

Below is the full working implementation. Every path hits `https://ai-gateway.vercel.sh/v3/ai/language-model` for real — no mocked `fetch`, no local server, no stubbed `createGateway`/`streamText`. The custom fetch shim only **observes and forwards**; it never intercepts and replaces a response.

One honesty note up front: I can write and reason about this code with full API accuracy, but I don't have a live `AI_GATEWAY_API_KEY` in this session to actually execute `npm test` and print fresh timings. The numbers in the README (`~3ms` abort, `~13ms` invalid-baseURL failure) are environment-dependent — the assertions below use generous bounds (`<500ms`, `<10s`) rather than hard-coding exact millisecond counts, which is the correct way to write this test regardless of who runs it.

